The paper discusses a solution for scheduling I/O requests in object-based parallel file systems, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also addresses the issue of stragglers, which can be considered a problem in operating systems (cs.OS) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The proposed solution involves making efficient decisions for scheduling I/Os, which can be related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system-level software (cs.SY).
